# Mission
Build the Legal Document Navigator: a multi-tenant platform where users upload their own
legal documents and get grounded, clause-cited answers. It is a document COMPREHENSION
tool, never legal advice. Keep a visible "understand your documents, not legal advice"
disclaimer in the UI.

# Architecture boundaries
- Next.js is a thin frontend and BFF: UI, Clerk sessions, presigned upload requests, simple
  reads. No business logic. It never writes to the database directly.
- FastAPI is the single backend brain: all ingestion, retrieval, AI calls, and business logic.
- Postgres is the single source of truth. FastAPI owns the schema and all writes.
- Heavy work (parse, chunk, embed) runs only in the async worker, never inline in a request.

# How to work
- Follow docs/BUILD_PLAN.md phase by phase. Do not skip phases or add unrequested features.
- Keep the app runnable and tested at every step. Make small, focused changes.
- Never hardcode secrets or model names. Never weaken tenant isolation for convenience.
- When unsure, follow existing patterns and ask before deviating from these rules.
